
[1]abelians

   ABE'LIANS, ABELO'NIANS or A'BELITES, in Church history, a sect in
   Africa which arose in the reign of Areadius; they married, but lived in
   continence after the manner, as they pretended, of Abel, and attempted
   to maintain the sect by adopting the children of others.
